Subject: [PATCH] Add data-driven AI layer: closed-loop planner, new-customer
 priority, propensity, feedback
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Builds on the revenue-at-risk + AI copilot work with five data-driven upgrades:

1. Closed-loop AI planner — after a CSR logs what a customer said, the AI
   decides the next move (channel, timing, angle) and pre-drafts the next
   message. Stored in ai_plans; surfaced on the card; the ✨ AI button uses
   the planned message instantly. Edge function gains a "plan" mode.

2. New-customer protection — first-time buyers (not yet repeat) jump ahead on
   the list, get a 🆕 badge and a caution note; winning the 2nd order is
   treated as the highest-leverage move.

3. True per-customer messages — the full follow-up history is passed to the
   copilot, so drafts are specific, never one-template-for-all.

4. Likely-to-order-soon — roDue() scores each customer's propensity from their
   personal rhythm; a 🔥 hot list, chip filter, pills, and dashboard tile.

5. Feedback collection — a ⭐ capture sheet logs rating + comment (feedback
   table); low ratings raise churn risk and flag recovery, high ratings push
   to review; dashboard shows average rating.

New Supabase tables (feedback, ai_plans) via supabase/ai-upgrade.sql. Every DB
call is best-effort — until the tables exist the app runs on local data and
never errors.

Verified: inline scripts parse clean; roDue/pills/plan/overlays exercised in a
headless browser with no JS errors.
